  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="acrostic_poem">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <p>
      <table>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>I</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>In chiefest time of Sommers spring,</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>O</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>Our Gardens then we make,</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>H</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>Hearing how cherping Birds doe sing,</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>N</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>No pleasure els we take.</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell cols="2"> </cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>S</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>So hauing set but sundry sprinks,</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>H</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>Hearbs flowers in their kind,</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>O</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>Of friendship had my Muse still thinks,</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>R</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>Reason driue it in my mind.</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>T</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>This Garland then I made with flowers,</cell>
         </row>
         <row>
            <cell>
               <hi>E</hi>
            </cell>
            <cell>Each branch sprung vp with Aprill showers.</cell>
         </row>
      </table>
   </p>
   <trailer>FINIS.</trailer>
</div>
